      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">3</infon>
        <offset>156</offset>
        <text>Nature is usually assumed to respond to gradual change in a smooth way.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">4</infon>
        <offset>228</offset>
        <text>However, studies on lakes, coral reefs, oceans, forests and arid lands have shown that smooth change can be interrupted by sudden drastic switches to a contrasting state.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">5</infon>
        <offset>399</offset>
        <text>Although diverse events can trigger such shifts, recent studies show that a loss of resilience usually paves the way for a switch to an alternative state.
</text>
        <annotation id="T7">
          <infon key="brat-id">T7</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
